The attack was discovered, continuously observed and analysed by thyssenkrupp´s CERT. Chief Information Officers of all Business Areas have been involved. All of thyssenkrupp´s IT systems are being controlled for new attempted attacks. The executive board of thyssenkrupp AG has been informed about the incident timely and continuously. At present there is no reliable estimation as to the damage caused by the attack. It has been noted that fragments of data have been stolen in the areas involved in the attack. The incident is not attributable to security deficiencies at thyssenkrupp. In a recent survey by the Federal Office for Information Security, 66 percent of participating companies reported they had been the target of hacking attacks.